					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the fourth pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 13: 919-20 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records an endowmeṉt of 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold on Saṅkrānti day by Kōyilāṉāchchipiḍāriyār, wife of Śembiyan Mūvēndavēḷār for food offerings to the deity Tirumaṟaikkāṭṭu-mādēvar from out of the interest accruing from the endowed amount.</p>						

						</summary>
